<item>
            <title>[SPR-2775] form:errors not allowed in a nested JSP outside the scope of form:form</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-2775</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The assertion in ErrorsTag.java:  onWriteTagContent() is assuming that the form:form tag is in the same document as the one being processed.  This effectively disallows JSP nesting and reuse when it is necessary to have the form:form tag outside the nested page.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not sure if this really IS a bug.  I know it is a safety mechanism but the case can also be made it gets in the way.  &lt;/p&gt;
</description>
